# Self-Review Checklist

<!--
Copy this checklist into a comment on your PR before requesting review.
Mark items as you verify them. This shows reviewers you've done a thorough check.
-->

## Description Accuracy
- [ ] PR description accurately describes all files in the diff
- [ ] No surprises or drift between description and actual changes

## Scope
- [ ] All files in the diff are intentionally included (no accidental files)
- [ ] No unrelated changes mixed in (single concern)
- [ ] No files changed that don't belong in this PR

## Artifact Cleanup
- [ ] No leftover `console.log`, `print`, `println` debug output
- [ ] No `debugger` or `pdb` breakpoints left behind
- [ ] No commented-out code blocks
- [ ] No TODO, FIXME, HACK, or XXX comments left unresolved
- [ ] No `.only` or `.skip` on test cases (all tests run)

## Test Coverage
- [ ] Every changed function/method has at least one corresponding test
- [ ] New tests are included in the diff
- [ ] All tests should pass (locally verified if possible)

## Single Concern
- [ ] Changes are focused on a single, logical concern
- [ ] No mixing of unrelated changes (auth + refactoring, etc.)
- [ ] If multiple concerns detected: consider splitting this PR

